import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['origin'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between different origin airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].median(), color='green', label='Median distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['count'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between flight count and distance?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
